### Description

I have a simple Windows Forms application which allows to drag text from label and drop to textbox. The text does appear in the textbox after dragging and dropping. However, the value of `effect` for some reason was `None`, and I got `Drop failed` message. I decided to check .NET 9 - everything works. Only in .NET 10 it fails to get correct value.

### Reproduction Steps

1. Run code below.
2. Drag text from label to textbox.
3. The text "LABEL TEXT" must appear in the textbox.
4. Message `Data has been copied!` must appear.

Full form code with all necessary elements:
